{
  "texts": [
    "We formulate it as an MDP under a classic RL scenario following [14,37], where an agent (investor) interacts with an environment (the financial market) to make actions (investment decisions) at discrete time to earn rewards (profits).",
    "The MDP is constructed by a 5-tuple (S, A, T, 𝑅, 𝛾).",
    "Specifically, S is a finite set of states.",
    "A is a finite set of actions.",
    "The state transition function T: S×A ×S → [0, 1] encapsulates transition probabilities between states based on chosen actions."
  ]
}